Bluetongue, Bosnia and Herzegovina
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 4 Nov 2014 from Dr Ljubomir Kalaba, Director, Veterinary Office, Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Relations, Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Oct 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 30 Oct 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: September 2003
Manifestation of disease: clinical infection
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: not typed
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Rasovac, Trebinje
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Oct 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 180 / 3 / 3 / 0 / -
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate
Sheep / 1.67 / 1.67 / 100 /

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors
Control measures
Measures applied: vaccination prohibited, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: control of arthropods, movement control inside the country

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Veterinary Institute "Dr Vaso Butozan" (local laboratory) / Sheep / enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 30 Oct 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

